{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"perovskite-frilly-grebe","description":"## Why\nAutomate the FFO rebase-to-tip-then-submit so parallel agent sessions stop hand-rolling it and racing; serialize so the tested tree is always the merged tree with no thrash.\n## What\nA project service (Python, project infra — NOT `src/rebar` core) that, for the front `Autosubmit`+submittable change/chain: rebases to the current tip, awaits a fresh `Verified +1`, and ancestor-atomic submits the exact tested SHA. Holds a single in-flight `wipChain`.\n## Scope\nHappy-path loop + serialization + identity/attribution. Failure paths, deploy, and the agent-facing command are separate stories.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Selects the front `label:Autosubmit+1 is:submittable` change/chain (FIFO, oldest-submittable-first).\n- [ ] Rebase to tip: `POST /changes/{id}/rebase` for ordinary + `--no-ff` merge changes (first-parent-only → `MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE`), `POST /rebase:chain` for relation chains; `on_behalf_of_uploader=true` preserves author/DCO `Signed-off-by`/`rebar-ticket` trailer.\n- [ ] Awaits a fresh `Verified +1` on the rebased patchset before submit (`LLM-Review` carries `TRIVIAL_REBASE`/`MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE` per ADR-0041; `Verified` re-runs).\n- [ ] Ancestor-atomic submit of the exact tested SHA; re-verify `is:submittable` immediately before `POST /submit`.\n- [ ] Single `wipChain` / single instance (serialized) — never rebases multiple changes onto the same HEAD concurrently.\n- [ ] Reads existing `Verified` votes only; casts NO votes (no gate-semantics change in Phase 1).","id":"0ee8-08de-bf0f-45ec","parent_id":"f1fa-57d8-07cb-44af","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"S2 Serial auto-lander core loop (rebase:chain -> await Verified -> ancestor-atomic submit)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783721677342858001,"uuid":"9b0b205e-fbe9-46e0-b941-76d19d496fa5"}